Standing check — each turn, before you respond: a skill is easy to pass over when the user names no skill and types no command, even when the moment is exactly what the skill is for. Pause and ask whether the current moment calls for one of your available skills — especially the session-management ones that act at boundaries: work crossing to a new goal or a fresh session, or a working context grown heavy. If one clearly fits, invoke it rather than handling the moment by hand. If none fits, just proceed — don't force a skill where it doesn't belong.
